llback() made in tested code.\n      After starting the inner transaction, we install a listener on transaction end events,\n      and each time the inner transaction is closed, we restart a new transaction to catch\n      potential new commit() / rollback().\nNote: When we rollback the inner transaction at the end of the test, we actually rollback\nonly the last inner transaction but previous inner transaction may have been committed by the\ntested code! This is why we need an outer transaction to rollback all changes made by the test."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.plugin", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.db", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.cor_hobby_child", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Parent", "bases": ["db.Model"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Parent.pk", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Parent.col", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Hobby", "bases": ["db.Model"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Hobby.__tablename__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Hobby.pk", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Hobby.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "utils_flask_sqla.tests.test_schema.Address", "bases": ["db.Model"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "utils_flask_sqla.